                        "content": "The nurse is preparing for the admission to the unit of a client with a diagnosis of seizures and asks the nursing student to institute full seizure precautions. Which item if noted in the client's room would need to be removed and warrants the need to review seizure precautions with the student?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "c2472dbaf30269ec1d4a4af474a31869",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Understanding 理解",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nFull seizure precautions include bed rest with padded side rails in a raised position, a suction machine at the bedside, having diazepam or lorazepam available, and providing an oxygen source. Objects such as tongue blades are contraindicated and would never be placed in the client's mouth during a seizure.",
